    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-16T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-16T14:00:00-05:00" n="511"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.23/1165: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-16T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >February 16, 1933—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 16—4:10 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>115. I have conveyed the information in your 68, February 15, 1 p.m.<note n="27"
                        xml:id="d511fn27">Not printed.</note> to Drummond. He now informs me that he
                    has just received <pb facs="0570" n="482" xml:id="pg_482"/> the same information
                    from the Colombian representative and that the Council Committee has sent a
                    message this afternoon to Lima asking for immediate information as to
                    hostilities which are taking place on Colombian territory.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
